column5: Got back last night from Manitou Falls. River was really low. All of the lakes were accessible but challenging. Fishing was good as always. Our group of 6 fished for 5 days. We caught a bunch of walleyes, 137 >20", largest was 27.75 inches. We also caught several northerns >30", largest being 39". If you are heading that way, don't forget the mosquito repellent! Dan M
Did ya get down to unexpected lake??
We did. It was really shallow (1.5 to 2 ft) going in and out but doable.
Unexpected, Johnson and Clear were all shallow getting in, shallower later in the week, fishing was stupid good, we tried to find lures that didnt work , never did find one of those
If your trying to find lures that won't work,soak them in gasoline,you'll probably hit the jack pot of non working lures.
I will keep that in mind
